## 2. SDD Workflow

Before making any changes, read in this order:

1. `.specify/memory/constitution.md`
2. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/spec.md`
3. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/plan.md`
4. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/tasks.md`

## 3. Rules

- `.specify/` is the source of truth.
- Do not implement features not described in `spec.md`.
- Follow `plan.md` for architecture and sequencing.
- Work task by task based on `tasks.md`.
- Only work on pending checks (`- [ ]`) and mark them when truly complete.
- If no tasks are pending, validate consistency instead of re-implementing.
- After each change, explain what task was completed and which files were modified.
- In case of conflict: `constitution.md` > `spec.md` > `plan.md`.

## 4. Available Prompts

Prompts are in `.specify/prompts/`.
Custom prompts are in `.specify/prompts/custom/`.

| Prompt | Description |
|---|---|
| `execute-spec` | Run a full spec through the SDD workflow |
| `sync-agent` | Regenerate this AGENTS.md |
| `new-spec` | Create a new spec for a feature |

Run `sdd prompt list` to see all prompts.
Run `sdd prompt run <name> --var KEY=VALUE` to render a prompt.

